ia-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 24, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104qfp1665702719294.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qfp1665702719294.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qfp1665702719294.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"qfp1665702719294\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Enable an asynchronous interrupt message when the Uniface Server reconnects.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"qfp1665702719294__topic_d141623e1_d141624e1_d141625e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qfp1665702719294__p_d141626e1_d141627e1_d141628e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$NET_REESTABLISH_MSGID</span> {=} <var class=\"keyword varname\">MessageID</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"qfp1665702719294__section_nms_vgr_2wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d564853e62\">Arguments</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qfp1665702719294__p_d141632e1_d141633e1_d141634e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">MessageID</var>—string from 1 to 32 characters</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"qfp1665702719294__section_bdx_vgr_2wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d564853e74\">Defaults</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"qfp1665702719294__table_d16940e1_d16941e1_d16942e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Assignment file:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">client assignment files,\n                  <span class=\"ph filepath\">urouter.asn</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Section:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">[SETTINGS]</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Default value:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">None</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"qfp1665702719294__section_stb_wgr_2wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d564853e122\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qfp1665702719294__p_d141641e1_d141642e1_d141643e1\">If <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$NET_REESTABLISH_MSGID</span> is\n        specified, at the moment that a broken server connection has been re-established and the\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">‘... re-establishing connection to URouter ...’</code> text has been written to\n        the message frame, a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">postmessage</span> to the application shell’s\n        receiveMessage trigger.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qfp1665702719294__p_d141644e1_d141645e1_d141646e1\">This message will contain the following data:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"qfp1665702719294__ul_afk_shr_2wb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qfp1665702719294__li_d49943e1_d49944e1_d49945e1\">The message ID, available via\n            <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$msgid</span>, as specified in the assignment file setting </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qfp1665702719294__li_d49946e1_d49947e1_d49948e1\">The source of the message, available via\n            <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$msgsrc</span>, that identifies the form or component from which the message\n          was sent </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qfp1665702719294__li_d49949e1_d49950e1_d49951e1\">Message data, available via\n            <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$msgdata</span>, that will contain the name of the lowest level path\n          pointing to the network driver </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qfp1665702719294__p_d141647e1_d141648e1_d141649e1\">The fixed sequence of events will be:</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\" id=\"qfp1665702719294__ol_m1m_thr_2wb\">\n<li class=\"li\">The connection is re-established. </li>\n<li class=\"li\">If successful, a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">postmessage</span> is sent.</li>\n<li class=\"li\">The receiveMessage trigger of the application shell is executed.</li>\n<li class=\"li\">The remainder of the database network I/O is carried out.</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"qfp1665702719294__note_klc_gbs_5dc\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$NET_REESTABLISH_MSGID</span> is applicable to only\n        TCP connections.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wtd1665702577667.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>postmessage</a><p>Send a message from one component instance to another.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zhv1719424135134.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$msgid</a><p>Return the identifier for a message received from postmessage.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mlt1665702695130.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$msgsrc</a><p>Return the name of the component instance that sent the message.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/msq1665702577585.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$msgdata</a><p>Return the message data received from postmessage.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531240\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531240\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$NET_REESTABLISH_MSGID Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 24, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Enable an asynchronous interrupt message when the Uniface Server reconnects. $NET_REESTABLISH_MSGID {=} MessageID Arguments MessageID —string from 1 to 32 characters Defaults Assignment file: client assignment files, urouter.asn Section: [SETTINGS] Default value: None Description If $NET_REESTABLISH_MSGID is specified, at the moment that a broken server connection has been re-established and the ‘... re-establishing connection to URouter ...’ text has been written to the message frame, a postmessage to the application shell’s receiveMessage trigger. This message will contain the following data: The message ID, available via $msgid , as specified in the assignment file setting The source of the message, available via $msgsrc , that identifies the form or component from which the message was sent Message data, available via $msgdata , that will contain the name of the lowest level path pointing to the network driver The fixed sequence of events will be: The connection is re-established. If successful, a postmessage is sent. The receiveMessage trigger of the application shell is executed. The remainder of the database network I/O is carried out. Note: $NET_REESTABLISH_MSGID is applicable to only TCP connections. Related Links postmessage Send a message from one component instance to another. $msgid Return the identifier for a message received from postmessage. $msgsrc Return the name of the component instance that sent the message. $msgdata Return the message data received from postmessage. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}